spleen (a monospaced bitmap font)

Spleen is a monospaced bitmap font available in 6 sizes:

    * 5x8
    * 6x12
    * 8x16
    * 12x24
    * 16x32
    * 32x64

Each size is provided in the Glyph Bitmap Distribution Format (BDF),
and release tarballs contain the fonts in the following formats: PCF,
PSF (for the Linux console), OTB, OTF, WOFF, WOFF2, .dfont for macOS 
users, and FON for Windows users.

All font sizes contain all ISO/IEC 8859-1 characters (Basic Latin and 
Latin-1 Supplement Unicode block), Latin Extended-A characters, as well
as Box Drawing, Block Elements, and Braille Patterns Unicode blocks, 
except for the 5x8 and the 6x12 versions.

Due to character size constraints, the 5x8 version only contains 
printable ASCII characters, the Braille Patterns Unicode block, and 
light Box Drawing characters. Please also note that there is no OpenType
version for this size.

As of Spleen 1.8.0, there is now a 6x12 version containing the same 
Unicode blocks as the 5x8 version and the Latin-1 Supplement Unicode 
block.

As of Spleen 2.0.0, the 8x16, 16x32 and 32x64 versions have full support
for Code page 437 (IBM PC).

Spleen also has support for Powerline symbols out of the box.

The font name is a reference to Baudelaire.
